Seems like it could be related to #85499, so I cc'd @jackh726.

@Noah Lev thanks for that.

Jack did some great investigation. I think this issue is worth a I-nominate and these findings be discussed during the meeting. Do you agree with that @Jack Huey ?
I'm fine with nominating, but I'm not quite sure it's going to do anything.
Discussed during the T-compiler triage meetings here and here. Consensus seems to be that it can be let slip.

this has been re-prioritized because it's about to land on stable.

Given the previous T-compiler discussion (see comment), I think the evaluation can remain unchanged.
@apiraino I'm pretty sure this has been on stable since October (1.56)

ah yes thanks for the correction. it was already in beta at the end of september, so clearly ended up in stable. the stable-to-stable-regression label was added just now but it does not indicate any change in this regard
I removed I-prioritize since it was just added automatically when the labels were changed and wasn't an intentional prio' request AFAICT
